ation integriert werden kann, wie betroffene Bücher sowie die rechtmäßigen EigentümerInnen identifiziert werden können, wie die einzelnen Fälle und Exemplare bearbeitet werden und wie wichtig dabei die Verbreitung der Forschungsergebnisse und die Vernetzung mit anderen ist.  aThis book educates library staff on how to efficiently determine whether publications that are being processed as new acquisitions or in retrospective cataloguing were or could have been plundered during the Nazi period. Spreading today's knowledge about Nazi-era provenance research will be of great importance in coming years as specific research projects come to an end and the expertise of research staff risks being lost.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 4aBibliotheksgeschichte. 4aProvenance research. 4aProvenienzforschung. 4alibrary history. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Library & Information Science / General.2bisacsh1 aBauer, Bruno, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aStumpf, Markus, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Library and Information Science 2016z9783110485240oZDB-23-DGB0 cEPUBz97831103959690 cprintz978311031858640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311031863040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110318630423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110318630.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LB  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGBb2016  aZDB-23-DGGb2016